The evidence with the title 'Smoking kills - Better Health Channel ' says Smoking causes a range of cancers, as well as heart disease, stroke and emphysema.  ... In Australia, smoking kills around 15,000 people every year. This is estimated to be about 90 per cent of all drug-caused deaths.  ... And they will die on average 10 years earlier than people who do not smoke.  ... .. related information. 
